The project code will be hosted in a public repository on GitHub and deployed using Netlify.

This project will use Netlfiy functions to get data about a provided URL.
Documentation can be found at the following URL:
@Web https://docs.netlify.com/functions/overview/

The project will use Browserless and specifically their screenshot functionality.
Documentation can be found at the following URL: 
@Web https://docs.browserless.io/rest-apis/screenshot

If screenshots are taken, the resulting files will be stored in an Amazon Web Service S3 bucket.
Documentation on the Node.js SDK which can be used with Netlify function can be found at the following URL:
@Web https://docs.aws.amazon.com/sdk-for-javascript/v2/developer-guide/s3-node-examples.html

Data about the submitted URLs will be persisted using Turso.
Documentation of their TypeScript API can be found at the following URL:
@Web https://docs.turso.tech/sdk/ts/quickstart

The project uses Drizzle ORM.
Drizzle Schema documentation:
@Web https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/column-types/sqlite